## Recent Changes

### Terminal Stability Overhaul (February 2026) — Latest
17 fixes across 13 files. 183/183 tests pass. Net -155 lines.

**Core Fixes:**
- ✅ **useImperativeHandle getter pattern** - TerminalCore handle uses ES5 getters so `handle.terminal` always returns current ref (was returning stale `null`)
- ✅ **Removed dead `terminalsRef`** - 8 dead code paths eliminated from App.tsx; all terminal access now through `terminalRefs` handles
- ✅ **Layout schema fix** - Zod `window:layout` schema used `.int()` rejecting fractional 0-1 values, breaking all layout persistence
- ✅ **Orphaned CSS deleted** - Removed `terminal-base.css` and `terminal-xterm.css` (never imported, contained conflicting rules)

**Resize Pipeline:**
- ✅ **Atomic tmux resize** - Single tmux command with `\;` chain instead of two child processes
- ✅ **Server-side resize dedup** - 50ms coalescing timer in ConnectionManager prevents process flooding
- ✅ **Resize lock microtask release** - `Promise.resolve().then()` instead of nested RAF for same-frame unlock
- ✅ **Panel resize trigger** - useEffect fires global resize 220ms after panel state changes (matches CSS transition)
- ✅ **Pre-capture settle time** - Increased 50ms → 100ms in WindowManager

**Display & Layout:**
- ✅ **Overflow-y hidden** - WebGL handles scrolling; forced scrollbar was stealing column space
- ✅ **SplitView container transition** - `transition-[left,right] duration-200 ease-out` for smooth panel open/close
- ✅ **Backpressure fix** - OutputPipelineManager was checking buffer size after clear (always 0)
- ✅ **Canvas verification awaited** - useResizeCoordinator `executeResize` is now async

**Mobile:**
- ✅ **Containment softened** - `contain: strict` → `contain: layout style` on mobile (strict broke scrolling)
- ✅ **Keyboard transition suppression** - Prevents layout shift during keyboard open/close
- ✅ **Dead code cleanup** - Removed unused `animating` state, `waitForTransitions` function

